[I] A database-independent abstraction layer written in C

[T] Libdbi implements a database-independent abstraction layer in
[T] C, similar to the DBI/DBD layer in Perl. Writing one generic
[T] set of code, programmers can leverage the power of multiple
[T] databases and multiple simultaneous database connections
[T] by using this framework. The plugin architecture allows for
[T] new database drivers to be easily added by a third party with
[T] flexible licensing.

[U] https://libdbi.sourceforge.net/

